Package: mfrmr
Type: Package
Title: Many-Facet Rasch Model Estimation and Diagnostics in R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person(given = "Ryuya", family = "Komuro", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "ryuya.komuro.c4@tohoku.ac.jp",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-9205-0926"))
Description: Estimates many-facet Rasch models and produces diagnostics,
    reporting helpers, and reproducible analysis bundles using a native R
    implementation. Supports arbitrary facet counts, rating-scale and
    partial-credit parameterizations (Andrich, 1978
    <doi:10.1007/BF02293814>; Masters, 1982
    <doi:10.1007/BF02296272>), marginal maximum likelihood estimation via the
    EM algorithm (Bock and Aitkin, 1981 <doi:10.1007/BF02293801>) and joint
    maximum likelihood estimation, plus workflow helpers informed by
    many-facet Rasch measurement practice and 'FACETS' documentation
    (Linacre, 1994, ISBN 0-941938-02-6; Linacre, 2023,
    <https://www.winsteps.com/a/Facets-Manual.pdf>).
URL: https://ryuya-dot-com.github.io/mfrmr,
    https://github.com/Ryuya-dot-com/R_package_mfrmr
